FBIS3-54720 "drsov001_f_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 National Affairs Inflation Reached 70 Percent a Month in 1993 LD0201204694 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 2000 GMT 2 Jan 94 LD0201204694 Moscow Russian Television Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Ukrainian Cabinet of Ministers has instructed that all retail trade prices in the republic are to be rounded off to multiples of 10 as of 1 January. All trading organizations, whatever their form of ownership, are obliged, as previously, to accept one, three, and five coupon notes, although in future they will be withdrawn from circulation. Official sources say inflation in Ukraine reached 70 percent a month by the end of 1993, and the largest bank note, 100,000 karbovantsy, is worth approximately $3 at the market rate.
